cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and machine learning models for text segmentation. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it discusses the use of active learning for model training. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves the selection of text sentences for human annotations, and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it deals with the ranking and scoring of sentences from a text corpus.
